# Official Documentation First

When implementing or altering code that touches a framework, library, or service:

1. Consult **official vendor documentation** first.
2. Prefer current, vendor-recommended APIs and patterns.
3. Avoid deprecated APIs.
4. Do **not** rely on third-party blog posts or tutorials as the primary source.

## This repo (Next.js apps)

Use official docs for:

- [Next.js](https://nextjs.org/docs)
- [Supabase](https://supabase.com/docs)
- [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com)
- [Stripe](https://stripe.com/docs) (where used, e.g. helvety-store)
- [React](https://react.dev) when relevant
